The paper deals with the problem of temporal action localization in videos, which involves recognizing action categories and localizing their start and end times. This is a problem that is commonly studied in computer vision (cs.CV) and multimedia (cs.MM) research. The proposed method involves designing a novel Convolutional-De-Convolutional (CDC) network, which is a type of neural network architecture commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) research. The paper also discusses the use of end-to-end training, which is a common technique in natural language processing (cs.CL) and other areas of machine learning. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.CV and cs.MM, followed by cs.LG, cs.AI, and cs.CL.
